                        <interp inst="t18360104-name-125" type="given" value="CHARLES EDWARD"></interp>CHARLES EDWARD SPARROW</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a jeweller. I was on Holborn-bridge on the 24th of December, about nine o'clock at night—I felt some<lb></lb>thing at my pocket—I turned round, and saw the prisoner tucking some<lb></lb>thing up his trowsers—I collared him, and told him he had my handker<lb></lb>chief—he denied it, and afterwards gave it to me—I gave him into custody—this is my handkerchief—I felt it taken, and he was the nearest person to me.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183601040013"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found the handkerchief on Holborn-bridge—a woman saw me pick it up—she said she would come to Guildhall.</p>
